text: Velika Kladuša (, ; lit. "Great Kladuša") is a town in the canton of Una-Sana in Bosnia and Herzegovina. It is in the far northwest of Bosnia and Herzegovina. It is on the border with Croatia. As of 2013, it has a population of 40,419. Most of the people living there are ethnic Bosniaks who follow Islam. The town is 100% Muslim with all residents professing Islam. == References == Category:Settlements in Bosnia and Herzegovina
title: Velika Kladuša
